WEBVTT

00:34.492 --> 00:36.528
| wish we had more time.

01:07.317 --> 01:09.228
[STAFF CHATTERING]

01:16.785 --> 01:18.321
[SIGHS]

01:24.000 --> 01:25.661
Earth to Lois.

01:26.628 --> 01:29.586
It's like you've been on another planet
for the last 15 minutes.

01:29.756 --> 01:30.996
[SCOFFS]

01:31.591 --> 01:34.298
Easy, Armstrong.
This space case is buried in research.

01:34.469 --> 01:37.506
I've got like two weeks' worth
of work to catch up on.

01:40.100 --> 01:42.432
It was sort of a last-minute vacation,
wasn't it?

01:43.269 --> 01:46.636
Yeah, well, I've got
a pretty tightly wound bolt reﬂex.

01:47.732 --> 01:49.518
Is this about what happened?

01:55.198 --> 01:57.359
Are you turning red?

02:00.829 --> 02:05.243
Believe it or not, my ejector-seat
malfunction wasn't totally about you.

02:05.959 --> 02:07.495
We should talk about it.

02:07.669 --> 02:10.536
When I wanna talk about it,
I'll send up a smoke signal.

02:11.172 --> 02:14.130
Excuse me. Can you help me?
I need a signature.

02:14.300 --> 02:16.632
I've got a delivery out back
and nobody's in yet.

02:26.146 --> 02:29.730
Ho, ho, ho, merry Christmas to me.

02:30.817 --> 02:33.604
-You want me to help you with this?
-No.

02:33.778 --> 02:36.645
Did I ever tell you that
| used to unwrap my presents...

02:36.823 --> 02:39.280
...and rewrap them
while my parents were sleeping?

02:39.450 --> 02:42.613
You know what, Lois,
that doesn't surprise me at all.

02:45.498 --> 02:47.079
[MUMBLING]

02:48.168 --> 02:50.159
[GASPS]

02:50.503 --> 02:52.880
-Just what I've always wanted.
-ls that—?

02:53.047 --> 02:55.629
I don't think it's powdered sugar,
Smallville.

02:56.676 --> 02:57.836
Lois Lane, Daily Planet.

02:58.011 --> 03:02.254
Care to comment on what illegal activities
got you trussed up like a turkey?

03:02.432 --> 03:05.720
I'm a cop. We're all undercover cops.

03:06.728 --> 03:08.059
Our sting went south.

03:08.229 --> 03:10.220
Someone thought
you were the real dealers.

03:10.398 --> 03:13.515
Who could be responsible
for such a super screwup?

03:13.693 --> 03:15.900
WOMAN:
Hey, there's something on the building.

03:16.112 --> 03:18.148
Who do you think did it?

03:18.323 --> 03:20.689
MAN:
It's amazing.

03:20.867 --> 03:22.983
WOMAN:
That is the Blur.

03:24.245 --> 03:27.282
Now, that's what I call a scoop.

04:24.931 --> 04:28.264
The Blur doesn't call for weeks,
now he's ovemighting our boys in blue.

04:28.434 --> 04:32.018
He's probably in the stratosphere
because he doesn't have his go-to girl.

04:32.188 --> 04:35.180
No way the botched save is a work
of the Blur. It's not his M0.

04:35.358 --> 04:37.440
I'll admit sugar-coating
is not his style...

04:37.610 --> 04:40.773
...but the 20-story calling card
was unmistakable.

04:40.947 --> 04:43.859
I'm beginning to lose faith
in our resident hero.

04:44.033 --> 04:47.275
You're breaking my heart.
I need a feature on the Blur's tactics...

04:47.453 --> 04:50.240
-...by the end of the day.
-You don't think this is big news?

04:50.415 --> 04:52.781
Turns out Adrian Pope,
the organized-crime boss...

04:52.959 --> 04:56.952
...is on the street because of the
Blur's blunder. The DA is out for blood.

04:57.130 --> 04:58.745
When is the DA not out for blood?

04:58.923 --> 05:01.380
He's just trying to cover up
his dirty connections.

05:01.551 --> 05:03.633
Listen, I am not your Blur girl
on this one.

05:03.803 --> 05:05.543
Just run with it.

05:05.722 --> 05:09.556
Listen, just see this as an opportunity
to investigate both sides of the story.

05:09.726 --> 05:11.887
That would require
a certain super someone...

05:12.061 --> 05:15.428
...to actually ﬁnd ﬁve minutes
to give me a call.

05:17.692 --> 05:19.057
What's with the disguise?

05:19.235 --> 05:21.692
All my ﬂannel is at the dry cleaners.
Go ﬁgure.

05:21.863 --> 05:24.605
-Lois.
-Pst! Leave it alone, Inspector Gadget.

05:26.034 --> 05:29.071
I have a top-secret interview
for an exposé on the hush-hush.

05:29.245 --> 05:31.327
So don't follow me.

05:39.047 --> 05:40.378
Could you lose the notebook?

05:40.548 --> 05:44.416
I would prefer that all our meetings
remain off the record.

05:45.470 --> 05:48.462
Whatever makes you feel
more comfortable, Lois.

05:52.435 --> 05:54.596
[SIGHS THEN CLEARS THROAT]

05:55.521 --> 06:00.015
Why don't you start by describing
these dreams you've been having?

06:03.154 --> 06:06.942
Okay. Well, they're as real
as you and me right now.

06:07.116 --> 06:08.572
More real, actually.

06:08.743 --> 06:12.406
And despite some ﬂashes
of some serious NC-17 violence...

06:12.580 --> 06:16.869
...really, the situation involves clothes
coming off.

06:17.043 --> 06:21.082
You know, naked skin.
Skin on skin. Just--

06:21.464 --> 06:22.579
[CLEARS THROAT]

06:22.757 --> 06:25.169
Lots of skin.

06:27.261 --> 06:29.718
So it's a sex dream...

06:29.931 --> 06:32.843
...with the coworker
you mentioned before?

06:33.017 --> 06:34.427
Clark Kent?

06:35.061 --> 06:36.676
What is this, Nightline?

06:36.854 --> 06:40.017
All right, yes, I'm doing the virtual
Kama Sutra with Clark Kent.

06:40.191 --> 06:43.024
My desk is soft-core central.

06:43.194 --> 06:47.312
Listen, Lois. You came to me to explore
the deeper meaning...

06:47.490 --> 06:49.776
...within these vivid dreams
you've been having.

06:49.951 --> 06:52.863
And all of this
doesn't have to be taken literally.

06:53.037 --> 06:57.246
A lack of clothing in a dream can signify
the desire to uncover...

06:57.417 --> 06:59.373
...what's actually hidden.

07:00.503 --> 07:04.337
You know, sometimes I do feel
that Clark is hiding something.

07:04.882 --> 07:06.463
[SIGHS]

07:09.720 --> 07:11.631
It sounds crazy...

07:11.806 --> 07:14.548
...but the closer I get to him,
the more...

07:14.976 --> 07:17.592
...I feel like he's going to disappear.

07:19.021 --> 07:23.355
Could this have something to do with
your three weeks of blocked memory?

07:24.360 --> 07:27.397
Maybe you're trying
to protect yourself, Lois.

07:27.572 --> 07:30.484
Didn't you say that the last time
you opened up to someone...

07:30.658 --> 07:34.276
...your mysterious caller...

07:34.454 --> 07:35.694
...he vanished?

07:36.706 --> 07:39.288
[PHONE RINGTONE]
I need a hero

07:39.459 --> 07:40.790
[SIGHS]

07:40.960 --> 07:44.248
Till the end of the night
He’s gotta be strong

07:44.422 --> 07:48.415
Speak of the devil. The Halley's comet
of phone dating himself.

07:48.634 --> 07:50.545
[LAUGHING]

07:53.097 --> 07:54.507
Sayonara, super stud.

07:54.724 --> 07:55.884
[PHONE BEEPS]

07:56.142 --> 07:59.009
You still have strong feelings
for this mystery man.

07:59.187 --> 08:02.725
Please. Remember eight tracks
and rotary phones?

08:02.899 --> 08:05.561
That's him. Ancient history.

08:05.735 --> 08:09.353
The fact you haven't gotten that
news ﬂash means I'm wasting my time...

08:09.530 --> 08:12.067
...with all of this head-shrink,
mumbo-jumbo stuff.

08:12.241 --> 08:18.783
Lois, you have projected so much
onto this mystery caller.

08:20.041 --> 08:23.033
Maybe you should focus on the man
that's right in front of you.

08:28.382 --> 08:30.168
I can't believe she's not picking up.

08:30.343 --> 08:33.130
Freeze the girl out, she's gonna give you
a cold shoulder.

08:33.304 --> 08:36.967
After what happened with Corben,
I stopped calling for her own protection.

08:37.141 --> 08:40.349
I'm sorry, this is a really bad time
for your PR queen to go MIA.

08:40.520 --> 08:43.978
She's the only one who can tell the truth.
The Blur's not responsible...

08:44.148 --> 08:47.015
...for the failed drug bust
or the crime boss getting away.

08:47.193 --> 08:49.855
You need to get to work
on some spin-doctor magic.

08:50.029 --> 08:55.365
Whoever is posing as the Blur is a genius
at marketing and self-promotion.

08:55.535 --> 08:58.197
He's co-opted your brand.

08:58.371 --> 09:00.657
I'm not a brand.

09:03.751 --> 09:05.116
The Blur has a blog?

09:05.294 --> 09:07.376
And you Twitter
and you're on Facebook...

09:07.547 --> 09:11.005
...where you have 10,000 friends,
by the way.

09:11.175 --> 09:14.633
You've come quite a long way since
being scarecrowed in high school.

09:15.429 --> 09:17.715
Why go through so much trouble
to discredit me?

09:17.890 --> 09:20.882
Now, here's the hitch.
I think he's actually trying to help you.

09:21.060 --> 09:23.722
I discovered ﬁve messy
but successful saves...

09:23.896 --> 09:26.433
...obviously not done by you.

09:27.567 --> 09:31.151
And whether this person means well
or not, they need to be stopped...

09:31.320 --> 09:33.606
...before someone gets hurt.

09:47.211 --> 09:49.702
Pull over by the power station.

09:49.880 --> 09:52.371
Nice and easy.

09:52.633 --> 09:56.626
These ladies and I have a date
with destiny.

10:03.769 --> 10:04.804
[THUMPING]

10:04.979 --> 10:06.344
[G ROWLING]

10:07.732 --> 10:09.268
Gun it.

10:09.525 --> 10:11.140
[ENGINE REWING]

10:11.611 --> 10:12.646
Go!

10:16.324 --> 10:17.530
[TIRES SCREECHING]

10:21.245 --> 10:22.451
Unh!

10:26.417 --> 10:28.658
[G ROWLING]

10:42.933 --> 10:44.434
Ahh.

10:45.811 --> 10:47.642
[PANTING]

10:53.527 --> 10:55.904
-We did it.
-Did you see that guy's face?

10:56.072 --> 10:58.028
-Pretty slick, 2.
-Way to go aggro, J.

10:58.199 --> 11:02.067
Once the police see this, they'll be off
our backs for your cops-in-a-box idea.

11:02.244 --> 11:03.859
Hey, they were undercover.

11:04.038 --> 11:06.120
Think we should tie him up?

11:06.874 --> 11:09.536
He's out cold.
Let's just get some shots to upload.

11:09.710 --> 11:10.916
Okay.

11:11.087 --> 11:12.668
[CAMERA BEEPING]

11:14.298 --> 11:17.005
What are you doing? You're in the shot.
This is evidence.

11:17.176 --> 11:19.667
Gotta give props to the man.

11:21.389 --> 11:23.004
[SPRAY PAINT CAN HISSING,
CAMERA CLICKS]

11:25.101 --> 11:27.467
Come on, Zan. Let's ﬂy.

11:30.106 --> 11:31.812
[TRANSFORMER EXPLODING]

11:40.950 --> 11:42.110
BOTH:
Whoa.

11:48.708 --> 11:50.289
[CHATTERING]

11:50.459 --> 11:52.620
Two hours to get here
with the monorail down.

11:52.795 --> 11:54.831
Chalk another one up
to the blundering Blur.

11:55.005 --> 11:59.123
He may have stopped a diamond heist
but his blackout has crippled Metropolis.

11:59.301 --> 12:01.462
And the scavengers
have already started circling.

12:01.637 --> 12:02.968
SACKS:
No city can function....

12:03.139 --> 12:06.176
District Attorney Ray Sacks.
My pet research project.

12:06.851 --> 12:09.638
CLARK: Since when is a veteran DA
newsworthy?

12:09.812 --> 12:12.975
Since his Christmas card roster reads
like a Sopranos hit list.

12:13.149 --> 12:15.640
I call him "Saxophone."
He loves to blow his own horn.

12:15.818 --> 12:18.309
Susan, I'm not here
because I'm running for mayor.

12:18.487 --> 12:20.102
I'm here because it's a travesty...

12:20.281 --> 12:22.818
...this city has been brought
to its knees by the Blur.

12:22.992 --> 12:25.233
WOMAN:
But you can't deny the beneﬁts the Blur....

12:25.411 --> 12:28.824
I can't help but think there's more
to this story than people are seeing.

12:28.998 --> 12:32.365
I think it's pretty obvious.
The Blur is hitting a quarter-life crisis...

12:32.543 --> 12:35.580
...or his ego has gotten
really supersized.

12:35.755 --> 12:39.043
And you're sure he didn't try to call you
and explain himself?

12:41.177 --> 12:44.635
He called. I didn't pick up.

12:45.347 --> 12:47.759
Since when did you become
the Blur's big defender?

12:49.351 --> 12:51.342
He doesn't deserve
the silent treatment...

12:51.520 --> 12:54.011
...just because he's been out there
saving people.

12:54.899 --> 12:57.686
Of course you would say that, Clark.
You're a guy.

12:57.860 --> 13:01.068
The Blur can't expect me to be
his beck-and-call girl...

13:01.238 --> 13:03.194
...after weeks of no contact.

13:04.200 --> 13:05.360
MAN:
That's a frequency test.

13:05.534 --> 13:06.569
Stand by. Line check.

13:06.744 --> 13:09.201
I spy with my little eye
a potential witness.

13:11.123 --> 13:14.786
[MONKEY CHATTERING RINGTONE]

13:36.482 --> 13:40.395
-I totally tanked this one.
-Don't be so hard on yourself.

13:40.569 --> 13:43.902
-You're not the one who lost her phone.
-You sure you don't have it?

13:44.073 --> 13:47.110
I must have dropped it
back at the power plant.

13:47.284 --> 13:52.119
I know I sort of pulled you into this
but maybe we're just not hero material.

13:52.331 --> 13:53.912
[MONKEY CHATTERING RINGTONE]

13:58.504 --> 14:01.086
-lt's you, J.
-What?

14:01.924 --> 14:02.959
This can't be good.

14:04.009 --> 14:07.092
What if someone's already on to us?
What do we do?

14:07.638 --> 14:08.923
Time to motor.

14:09.098 --> 14:11.339
-Powers activate.
-Powers activate.

14:11.600 --> 14:14.012
[ZAN AND JAYNA GRUNT]

14:28.284 --> 14:30.866
Whoa. What the—?

14:32.496 --> 14:34.612
Where are we?

14:40.170 --> 14:42.877
How did we even get here?

14:43.048 --> 14:46.040
-It had to have been the Blur.
-No. Come on, 2, no way.

14:46.260 --> 14:49.673
Think about it.
Who else could have stopped us?

14:52.349 --> 14:56.137
-This is the Blur's lair.
-He doesn't have a lair.

14:56.312 --> 14:59.804
I'm telling you, this tech
is deﬁnitely off the grid.

14:59.982 --> 15:02.394
Wait until I tweet everybody
about this.

15:02.568 --> 15:04.559
CHLOE:
That's not gonna happen.

15:06.030 --> 15:07.270
Welcome to Watchtower.

15:08.908 --> 15:11.320
If you chat one word
about what you see in here...

15:11.493 --> 15:14.326
...I will vaporize your Twitter accounts,
Facebook pages...

15:14.496 --> 15:18.205
...every trace of your virtual existence
will be obliterated.

15:18.375 --> 15:21.538
Holy hacking. You can do that?

15:22.379 --> 15:26.167
-Our tweets are totally sealed.
-Code of silence. All the way.

15:26.342 --> 15:27.548
So who are you?

15:27.718 --> 15:28.958
Oh, it's the Blur's sidekick.

15:29.136 --> 15:30.421
[WHISPERS]
We don't know that.

15:30.596 --> 15:32.837
Not exactly.
I'm doing pro bono for the Blur...

15:33.015 --> 15:34.676
...and keeping an eye on you two.

15:34.850 --> 15:37.216
[IN NORMAL VOICE] Wait. You're
not gonna hand us over to the cops?

15:37.394 --> 15:40.101
We just wanted to help,
fuel the Blur's legend.

15:40.314 --> 15:43.852
Okay, about the helping.
Right idea, wrong execution.

15:44.026 --> 15:45.857
I've been where you guys are. I get it.

15:46.028 --> 15:48.770
You're just mega-fans
who really wanna make a difference.

15:48.948 --> 15:52.736
But you are single-handedly
destroying what the Blur stands for.

15:57.581 --> 16:00.948
We know we've made some mistakes.

16:01.126 --> 16:03.117
How do we make up
for what we've done?

16:04.129 --> 16:08.213
You just wait for the right moment.
You'll know.

16:09.426 --> 16:12.133
So the Blur trusts you, right?

16:13.347 --> 16:15.804
I mean, how do you always know
the right thing to do?

16:15.975 --> 16:20.059
You don't. And neither does he.

16:20.396 --> 16:24.730
But you stick around a hero long enough
and you get your share at saving him.

16:25.067 --> 16:27.934
Sometimes even from himself.

16:38.872 --> 16:40.737
Oh, man.

16:42.251 --> 16:44.663
I don't know how old-school journalists
broke a story...

16:44.837 --> 16:46.873
...without breaking somebody's neck.

16:47.923 --> 16:50.460
MAN:
Yeah. All right.

16:51.510 --> 16:54.593
I will never take you for granted again.
I swear.

16:55.514 --> 16:57.800
[PHONE RINGTONE]
I need a hero

16:57.975 --> 17:01.433
I'm holding out for a hero
Till the end of the night

17:01.895 --> 17:03.146
[SIGHS]

17:03.313 --> 17:04.439
[PHONE BEEPS]

17:04.982 --> 17:07.598
I suppose you were the one
who gave us that reboot.

17:07.776 --> 17:11.109
CLARK: In a way, the city going dark
was my fault.

17:11.613 --> 17:13.945
Least I could do was put things right.

17:14.116 --> 17:17.779
Just because you threw a few switches
doesn't make up for your bonehead moves.

17:17.953 --> 17:19.614
Lois...

17:20.497 --> 17:22.283
...I wasn't the one behind the saves.

17:22.458 --> 17:24.619
The Blur has an imposter nipping
at his heels?

17:24.793 --> 17:26.294
How did you let that happen?

17:26.462 --> 17:27.998
It's not that simple.

17:29.465 --> 17:30.955
They were just misguided fans.

17:31.467 --> 17:33.549
[IN BLUR'S VOICE]
I 'rn not turning them over to the DA.

17:33.719 --> 17:36.552
Without proof, nobody's gonna buy
the "misguided fans" angle.

17:36.722 --> 17:40.214
You're risking a lot to protect
some feckless meteor freaks.

17:40.434 --> 17:44.143
Maybe. But doesn't everyone deserve
a second chance?

17:46.356 --> 17:47.687
Oh, you wanna go there?

17:47.858 --> 17:49.974
Let me tell you
about second chances, buddy.

17:50.152 --> 17:52.689
There's a way you treat a woman.
It's called respect.

17:52.863 --> 17:54.478
How did you end up on the street?

17:54.656 --> 17:57.398
For a long time now
we've only had each other, so....

17:57.576 --> 18:00.033
Nobody really bought us
as transfer students from Sweden.

18:00.204 --> 18:01.284
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

18:01.455 --> 18:05.869
That taps into cell phone frequencies.
Just don't touch anything, okay?

18:06.043 --> 18:07.533
ZAN:
Sorry.

18:09.254 --> 18:11.836
-Just because you're some fancy hero-
-Lois, I tried.

18:12.007 --> 18:13.668
There is no "try," Skywalker.

18:13.842 --> 18:16.333
You have super-powers.
Why don't you pick up a phone?

18:16.512 --> 18:17.843
Lois...

18:18.013 --> 18:19.844
[BLUR'S VOICE BREAKING UP]
.y..ou're just gonna have to do something...

18:20.015 --> 18:21.551
.y..ou've had trouble with lately.

18:22.392 --> 18:24.303
[IN CLARK'S VOICE]
You're gonna have to trust me.

18:24.478 --> 18:25.718
[PHONE DISCONNECTS]

18:26.480 --> 18:28.391
[WHISPERS]
Smallville.

18:34.029 --> 18:35.860
[COWS MOOING]

18:36.824 --> 18:38.985
Last night was a whirlwind
of happy endings...

18:39.159 --> 18:42.026
...as Metropolis' Blur worked overtime
to bring the city...

18:42.204 --> 18:44.661
...out of the darkness
and into the light.

18:46.834 --> 18:50.201
Lois. I didn't realize you were ﬁlling in
for the paperboy.

18:50.420 --> 18:51.705
[CHUCKLES]

18:51.880 --> 18:55.668
Ahem. You look pretty chipper.
Busy night?

18:55.843 --> 18:58.425
My story about the Blur
made it above the fold.

18:58.637 --> 19:02.050
I think he'd be pretty happy
that I included his side of the story.

19:04.643 --> 19:06.679
-So you ﬁnally heard from him.
-Yeah.

19:07.187 --> 19:10.054
Anyway, I've been thinking a lot
about my carbon footprint...

19:10.232 --> 19:13.395
...and I ﬁgured, you know,
we could start carpooling.

19:15.279 --> 19:17.895
I thought, you know, the ride...

19:18.073 --> 19:22.612
...would give us a chance to get past
the whole "kiss and run" of it all...

19:22.786 --> 19:24.572
...and get to know each other better.

19:25.080 --> 19:26.866
3535?}

19:27.249 --> 19:31.743
You tell me the color of your underwear
every day. What else is there to know?

19:35.716 --> 19:39.959
I hope you didn't misunderstand
all my Blur-bashing I did yesterday.

19:40.179 --> 19:41.885
Deep down, I never doubted him.

19:44.725 --> 19:48.434
I'm sure he'd be happy to learn
that your faith in the Blur never wavered.

19:50.564 --> 19:53.931
Of course, he never explained
why he didn't call me back.

19:55.569 --> 19:57.434
Lois, what's going on?

20:01.700 --> 20:03.691
Okay, look...

20:04.411 --> 20:06.697
...I woke up this morning...

20:07.789 --> 20:10.701
...and I saw things clearly
for the ﬁrst time.

20:13.921 --> 20:15.707
REPORTER [ON TV]:
In breaking news...

20:15.881 --> 20:17.997
...Metropolis' DA has called out the Blur.

20:18.217 --> 20:21.505
SACKS [ON TV]: No one has the right
to take the law into their own hands.

20:21.720 --> 20:24.928
Not you, not me, not even the Blur.

20:25.974 --> 20:28.761
Now, because of the damage
he has caused this city...

20:28.936 --> 20:32.428
...I am asking the Blur to come out
of the shadows...

20:32.606 --> 20:37.441
...to stop this vigilante behavior,
and agree to work hand-in-hand...

20:37.611 --> 20:40.318
with our law enforcement.

20:40.489 --> 20:45.028
Now, I will be holding a press conference
later this afternoon.

20:45.244 --> 20:50.034
At that time,
I will ask the Blur to show himself...

20:50.249 --> 20:54.242
...and to take responsibility
for his actions.

20:57.547 --> 21:00.539
Big news day. I'll have to take
a rain check on the carpooling.

21:03.178 --> 21:05.169
Okay.

21:06.265 --> 21:08.506
Dr. Evans—

21:10.018 --> 21:14.307
I'm going to save you a lot of time
and money, okay?

21:15.357 --> 21:17.348
It's all your parents' fault.

21:17.567 --> 21:19.398
[SOBBING]

21:27.536 --> 21:28.571
Marjorie?

21:29.288 --> 21:32.200
Oh, she had to take off. Family issues.

21:34.584 --> 21:37.166
You think you're good
at this head-shrinking stuff...

21:37.337 --> 21:40.579
...but thanks to you,
my head is about to explode...

21:40.799 --> 21:42.300
...and I don't know what to do.

21:44.386 --> 21:47.423
I focused on the man in my dreams
and now I found out...

21:47.597 --> 21:51.010
...that my mysterious caller and Clark
are the same person.

21:51.184 --> 21:52.924
-The same?
-Unbelievable.

21:53.103 --> 21:58.063
Up until today, he couldn't lie his way
out of a speeding ticket...

21:58.233 --> 22:01.270
...and now can hold down
an alter ego?

22:01.445 --> 22:03.356
Lois, take a step back.

22:03.530 --> 22:05.236
What do you think is more likely?

22:05.407 --> 22:08.695
That your mysterious caller and Clark
are the same man...

22:08.869 --> 22:11.281
...or that you're trying to make them
one person...

22:11.455 --> 22:13.241
...in order to create your dream man?

22:20.547 --> 22:21.912
Okay. They're not that different.

22:22.090 --> 22:24.422
My mysterious caller
is brave and selﬂess.

22:24.593 --> 22:26.925
And so is Clark...

22:27.220 --> 22:28.255
...in his own way.

22:29.431 --> 22:33.265
I can't believe how difﬁcult this must
have been for him to carry his secret...

22:33.435 --> 22:35.926
...all this time.

22:38.940 --> 22:41.932
I just wanna tell him
that it doesn't matter to me.

22:45.405 --> 22:49.944
But maybe coming clean
isn't the best idea either.

22:50.869 --> 22:54.737
Right now Clark has this really big
decision to make.

22:54.915 --> 22:57.281
And more than anything...

22:57.459 --> 23:01.122
...I just wanna help.
But I'm not sure how.

23:06.259 --> 23:07.419
Ha....

23:07.594 --> 23:10.677
Wait, I know what I have to do.

23:11.431 --> 23:13.968
Thanks, doc. You're a gem.

23:14.142 --> 23:17.305
There's gotta be something
to this therapy stuff.

23:25.445 --> 23:27.310
Clark. Hey.

23:27.489 --> 23:29.980
The Twittering twosome
have sung their last song.

23:30.158 --> 23:33.867
As we speak, they're in Watchtower
and taking down the Blur's blog.

23:34.037 --> 23:36.028
Have you seen today's news?

23:36.206 --> 23:38.697
Don't tell me you're taking
that blowhard seriously.

23:38.917 --> 23:41.659
You know he's just gunning
for the mayor's ofﬁce.

23:41.837 --> 23:44.294
You are, aren't you? Clark, why?

23:44.464 --> 23:49.003
The last time you had a coming-out party,
it was a disaster. What changed?

23:49.678 --> 23:52.511
I've changed.
I'm wearing my father's shield now.

23:52.681 --> 23:54.512
I've worked hard
to give people hope...

23:54.683 --> 23:58.050
...something that they can believe in,
that will inspire them.

23:59.146 --> 24:00.181
I am the shield.

24:00.355 --> 24:02.562
I know you wanna honor your father,
Clark...

24:02.732 --> 24:05.348
...but if you sacriﬁce yourself,
there is no shield.

24:05.527 --> 24:08.269
I won't do nothing while the DA drags
down my father's crest...

24:08.447 --> 24:09.903
...and everything it stands for.

24:10.073 --> 24:12.314
That's exactly what you have to do.
I'm sorry.

24:12.492 --> 24:14.869
This guy's gonna call you a menace
and a coward...

24:15.036 --> 24:16.867
...and probably a threat to the city...

24:17.038 --> 24:19.700
...and you have to let people believe
his lies.

24:20.333 --> 24:24.326
Your father lives on through you,
not your shield.

24:32.345 --> 24:34.472
MAN:
Ladies and gentlemen...

24:34.681 --> 24:37.172
...District Attorney Sacks.

24:38.226 --> 24:39.727
[CROWD MURMURING]

24:40.562 --> 24:44.851
Good afternoon.
Thank you all for joining me.

24:45.775 --> 24:48.733
If you're out there, Blur...

24:48.904 --> 24:50.690
...come.

24:50.864 --> 24:53.697
Come join me at this very podium...

24:53.867 --> 25:00.409
...and take your place as a role model
in this great city of ours.

25:00.582 --> 25:04.746
A true hero would not hide.

25:05.545 --> 25:07.627
He would show himself...

25:07.797 --> 25:11.415
...and take responsibility
for the mistakes he's made.

25:11.593 --> 25:12.799
LOIS:
Out of my way.

25:13.011 --> 25:14.751
Excuse me.
Move it or lose it.

25:14.930 --> 25:16.466
SACKS:
No, it's all right. Let her up.

25:16.640 --> 25:17.720
Zip it, counselor.

25:20.769 --> 25:25.433
I'm Lois Lane from the Daily Planet and
I'm here to tell you that I know the Blur.

25:25.607 --> 25:26.767
It's okay. It's okay.

25:30.153 --> 25:34.146
LOIS: The DA says that a true hero
would come forward.

25:35.742 --> 25:38.074
Well, the Blur can't.

25:38.954 --> 25:43.948
It's because he knows that the best way
for him to protect you and me...

25:44.125 --> 25:48.243
...is to steer clear
of all of this political hoopla...

25:49.297 --> 25:54.963
...and remain the one thing
that you and I need most...

25:55.470 --> 25:58.257
...a light in the darkness.

25:58.431 --> 26:03.425
A symbol for us to believe in
when all other hope is lost.

26:05.146 --> 26:07.979
I've looked into the Blur's heart...

26:08.316 --> 26:13.652
...and I can tell you
that his intentions are good.

26:14.322 --> 26:18.816
Let the Blur be the hero
he needs to be.

26:18.994 --> 26:20.609
[CROWD CLAPPING AND CHEERING]

26:38.221 --> 26:40.177
[SIGHS]

26:55.739 --> 26:59.027
When you said you had looked into
the Blur's heart...

26:59.200 --> 27:02.363
...I had no idea
how close a relationship you had.

27:04.247 --> 27:06.329
Not that it's any of your business.

27:06.499 --> 27:10.367
Oh, the safety of this city
is always my business, young lady.

27:10.545 --> 27:14.879
Now tell me the true identity
of the Blur...

27:15.050 --> 27:17.757
...and I'll overlook
your annoying antics.

27:17.927 --> 27:20.885
You talk a good game, counselor...

27:21.056 --> 27:23.718
...but you don't believe a word of it.

27:24.517 --> 27:27.099
All your shady backroom deals
with organized crime...

27:27.270 --> 27:28.851
...have just come home to roost.

27:29.022 --> 27:32.856
I've picked out a nice little font
for my expose:

27:33.026 --> 27:35.642
"Shady Sacks sucks the city dry."

27:38.281 --> 27:40.442
Well, well, well.

27:41.743 --> 27:45.782
I actually had another headline in mind.

27:47.582 --> 27:51.746
And you're standing right on top of it.

27:58.385 --> 28:02.378
"The Blur murders Lois Lane."

28:02.972 --> 28:05.588
Has a nice ring, doesn't it?

28:07.102 --> 28:08.933
Nobody will ever believe you.

28:09.104 --> 28:13.063
Honey, when the Blur decided
not to come fonrvard...

28:13.233 --> 28:16.225
...he put the ball back in my court.

28:16.403 --> 28:18.610
I can make him
whoever I want him to be.

28:18.780 --> 28:21.271
It just takes a little doubt.

28:23.493 --> 28:26.485
You don't give people enough credit.

28:26.705 --> 28:29.742
Why would the Blur suddenly turn
into a murderer?

28:30.458 --> 28:35.122
Because you just announced
in front of millions of people...

28:36.423 --> 28:40.132
...that you are the only person
who knows his true identity.

28:41.219 --> 28:42.379
Unh!

28:43.388 --> 28:48.007
Unh! Oh! You're the one who's hiding in
the shadows, not the Blur, you coward.

28:48.226 --> 28:51.639
Unfortunately, that's not a story
you're gonna get to write.

28:53.022 --> 28:54.637
Unh!

28:55.650 --> 28:56.856
[LOIS SCREAMS]

28:57.026 --> 28:59.233
All right, let's get out of here.

29:06.536 --> 29:07.901
Oh!

29:08.163 --> 29:10.825
[PANTING]

29:20.633 --> 29:22.214
BRADY:
Hey, Clark, you gotta see this.

29:22.385 --> 29:24.091
And grab a camera.

29:25.388 --> 29:27.470
I'll have to call you back.

29:27.640 --> 29:29.847
WOMAN: Hey, there's a woman
hanging from the building.

29:30.518 --> 29:32.679
LOIS:
Help! Somebody!

29:33.480 --> 29:34.515
Lois.

29:38.151 --> 29:39.857
Lois?

29:45.325 --> 29:46.861
Hold on, I'm coming.

29:49.037 --> 29:51.403
Clark. Help me.

29:52.832 --> 29:54.413
-Lois?
-Clark.

29:54.626 --> 29:55.661
Grab my hand.

29:55.877 --> 29:57.538
[GASPING]

29:57.754 --> 29:58.960
LOIS:
I can't.

29:59.130 --> 30:00.870
CLARK:
All right, hold on.

30:02.383 --> 30:03.509
[CLARK GRUNTS]

30:05.553 --> 30:07.214
I'm

30:07.430 --> 30:08.931
[CROWD GASPS]

30:10.350 --> 30:11.635
[LOIS WHIMPERING]

30:16.231 --> 30:18.893
Come on, stretch. You can reach.

30:19.067 --> 30:21.183
LOIS:
It's too far.

30:23.613 --> 30:24.648
Aah!

30:24.864 --> 30:26.400
Lois!

30:29.911 --> 30:31.242
[BUZZING]

30:46.177 --> 30:48.589
Hey, J. So, what's going on?

30:48.763 --> 30:51.254
The Blur's in even deeper
and it's all our fault.

30:51.432 --> 30:54.139
-Then what are we waiting for?
-We can't ditch Chloe.

30:54.310 --> 30:57.268
We promised her we'd lay low
till this all blows over.

30:57.438 --> 31:02.273
She said sometimes you need
to save a hero, even from himself.

31:02.819 --> 31:05.936
Dad always used to say
we're stronger when we stick together.

31:10.118 --> 31:11.949
-Powers activate.
-Powers activate.

31:15.790 --> 31:17.576
Lois, hold on.

31:20.295 --> 31:22.126
Let me go.

31:22.505 --> 31:24.120
That's insane, Lois.

31:24.841 --> 31:27.958
You can't reveal yourself
to the cameras.

31:28.136 --> 31:31.173
You mean too much to the city.

31:31.347 --> 31:32.598
To the world.

31:34.726 --> 31:35.932
Clark...

31:37.145 --> 31:41.309
...I know you've been living two lives and
having to lie to me about it every day.

31:41.482 --> 31:44.269
Lois, you're not making any sense.

31:44.527 --> 31:46.643
[WHOOSHING]

31:49.824 --> 31:53.032
It's gonna be okay. Just hold on.

31:55.663 --> 31:58.996
I've always known, deep down,
that you were a hero.

32:03.379 --> 32:05.335
Lois!

32:18.686 --> 32:20.142
What?

32:25.693 --> 32:27.194
[SIGHS]

32:34.160 --> 32:35.491
All right, let's go.

32:35.662 --> 32:37.118
[G ROWLING]

32:37.622 --> 32:39.203
[BARKING]

32:46.005 --> 32:47.586
Lois.

32:48.383 --> 32:49.543
You're alive.

32:52.845 --> 32:54.710
Thank you.

33:00.728 --> 33:02.559
I'm ﬂattered, Lois.

33:03.606 --> 33:05.938
I wish I could have been the one
to rescue you...

33:06.109 --> 33:08.316
...but I'm not that fast.
I took the elevator.

33:10.905 --> 33:13.692
Even after all this
you still can't tell me?

33:17.078 --> 33:19.034
[PHONE RINGING]

33:26.212 --> 33:28.453
Just stay here.

33:32.427 --> 33:34.918
BLUR [OVER PHONE]: Next time
you take on the DA of Metropolis...

33:35.096 --> 33:37.257
...remember to watch your step.

33:38.891 --> 33:42.759
-But that was just--
-Hope [made up for not calling.

33:46.274 --> 33:48.105
Lois, who was that?

33:51.946 --> 33:53.231
The Blur.

34:00.371 --> 34:02.987
JAYNA:
Yeah, the DA is TKO.

34:03.166 --> 34:06.124
-The Blur is back on top.
-This makes up for everything.

34:06.294 --> 34:08.125
CLARK:
I have you to thank for that.

34:11.007 --> 34:14.124
-Oh, my God.
-lt's him.

34:14.302 --> 34:17.089
I put my shield out there
to inspire people to step up...

34:17.263 --> 34:19.504
...be their own heroes.

34:19.682 --> 34:20.842
And you did.

34:22.310 --> 34:24.266
We believe in you, Master B.

34:25.438 --> 34:30.182
Don't believe in me, believe in the shield
and what it represents.

34:30.943 --> 34:33.980
Most importantly,
believe in yourselves.

34:34.822 --> 34:36.403
[BOTH SIGH]

34:37.450 --> 34:41.659
But we're not the hero, you are.

34:42.538 --> 34:44.574
That depends on you.

34:44.749 --> 34:46.580
Metropolis doesn't need
more Blur fans.

34:46.751 --> 34:50.164
It needs people who are willing to do
exactly what you did today.

34:52.882 --> 34:55.419
But you do need to be more careful.

34:56.636 --> 34:58.172
Heroes don't get second chances.

34:58.346 --> 35:02.214
And people need you to make
Iife-and-death decisions every day.

35:03.267 --> 35:05.428
There's no room for mistakes.

35:08.815 --> 35:09.895
Ever?

35:12.235 --> 35:14.317
Not when the world is watching.

35:23.913 --> 35:26.279
I am happy to see
that you're alive, Lois...

35:26.457 --> 35:29.073
...after what I saw
on the nightly news.

35:29.252 --> 35:30.412
[LOIS SCOFFS]

35:30.586 --> 35:33.419
I never would have guessed
that your mysterious caller...

35:33.589 --> 35:37.332
...was none other
than Metropolis' famous Blur.

35:38.052 --> 35:41.294
I can't believe I was so stupid.

35:41.472 --> 35:45.090
I must have been crazy to look at Clark
through Blur-colored glasses.

35:45.268 --> 35:47.600
Lois, you are not crazy.

35:47.770 --> 35:51.262
That's the point of therapy,
to learn about yourself.

35:51.440 --> 35:56.184
But just looking at the facts,
what's easier to believe?

35:56.362 --> 35:58.318
That there was some phone glitch...

35:58.489 --> 36:01.356
...or that the farm guy
who sits across from me every day...

36:01.534 --> 36:04.071
...is a super-powered hero?

36:05.830 --> 36:07.786
It's perfectly natural, Lois...

36:07.957 --> 36:12.200
...to project the heroics of the
unattainable men you tend to fall for...

36:12.378 --> 36:14.334
...onto someone close to you.

36:14.505 --> 36:18.999
It would be so much easier
if they were the same person.

36:21.179 --> 36:26.845
When I heard the Blur's voice again,
something stirred inside of me.

36:30.396 --> 36:32.978
But my thoughts...

36:35.985 --> 36:37.191
[SIGHS]

36:37.445 --> 36:40.528
...they keep going back to Clark...

36:40.823 --> 36:42.734
[CHUCKLES]

36:43.284 --> 36:45.696
...that scared guy...

36:45.870 --> 36:49.533
...who stepped out onto that ledge
to save me.

36:57.298 --> 36:58.708
CHLOE:
Hey.

36:58.883 --> 37:01.750
Cheers. For earning
another stripe today.

37:03.346 --> 37:04.461
Where did you get that?

37:04.639 --> 37:08.097
The street vendor on the corner.
It also comes in T-shirts and key chains.

37:08.768 --> 37:11.885
I had to be the ﬁrst one on the block
to get the superhero swag.

37:13.272 --> 37:16.184
Next thing you know, your wonder twins
will be a household name.

37:16.692 --> 37:19.980
Thanks to the fog-and-dog duo,
Sacks is on his way to the slammer.

37:20.154 --> 37:22.236
With training, they may give the Blur...

37:22.406 --> 37:24.567
...some needed backup
in the halls ofjustice.

37:24.742 --> 37:27.108
I guess I have more backup
than I thought.

37:27.620 --> 37:31.033
How'd you pull off
the whole "Blur impersonation" thing?

37:31.207 --> 37:35.951
Just your typical sleight-of-ear stuff.
Now you hear it, now you don't.

37:38.256 --> 37:39.837
BLUR'S VOICE [ON COMPUTER]:
Hello, Lois.

37:40.007 --> 37:43.124
Pay no attention
to the blond behind the curtain.

37:43.302 --> 37:46.385
Relax, Clark. I'm not exactly
the great and powerful Oz.

37:46.555 --> 37:50.298
I just created a program where
everything I type in here out comes Blur.

37:50.977 --> 37:53.719
But how'd you know
when to make the call...

37:53.896 --> 37:56.729
...and hoW'd you know
what to say to convince Lois?

37:57.483 --> 37:59.724
I hacked into the security cameras
on the rooftop.

37:59.902 --> 38:02.894
And I've been monitoring
all cell communication in Metropolis.

38:03.072 --> 38:06.564
You've been eavesdropping on
my personal calls with Lois, haven't you?

38:07.368 --> 38:11.236
Chloe, there's keeping a bird's-eye view
and then there's playing Big Brother.

38:11.414 --> 38:15.032
Easy on the dress-down, Clark, okay?

38:15.209 --> 38:18.952
If I hadn't, Lois would still be beating
down the "Clark is a superhero" door.

38:19.130 --> 38:23.169
And believe me, once the bloodhound
Lois is at your door...

38:23.342 --> 38:26.550
...you'd better ﬁnd a better way
to disguise your superhero scent.

38:39.984 --> 38:42.771
-Your eyes still closed?
-This isn't what I had in mind...

38:42.945 --> 38:47.154
...when you said you wanted to meet
in the copy room, but hey, I'm open.

38:47.325 --> 38:49.566
You said I had a secret.
You were right.

38:49.744 --> 38:51.905
I was dangling 100 stories
above the pavement.

38:52.079 --> 38:54.365
I think I get a free pass on that one.

38:56.625 --> 38:57.876
Let's see what you've got.

39:02.715 --> 39:04.376
I'm a bit nearsighted.

39:06.802 --> 39:08.884
I've been trying not to wear them.

39:10.890 --> 39:13.302
They're very...

39:20.816 --> 39:22.431
...Clark Kent.

39:25.237 --> 39:28.195
I guess you're not the only one
who's a little short-sighted.

39:28.366 --> 39:31.529
It's just sometimes I feel like
I see a whole other side of you...

39:31.702 --> 39:33.203
-...than anyone else.
-Lois?

39:33.371 --> 39:35.236
It's okay.

39:35.623 --> 39:38.535
It's my hero complex to resolve.

39:38.709 --> 39:43.499
I take the nicest guy that I know and
I weigh him down with shining armor.

39:43.672 --> 39:47.039
And it's not fair.
Nobody can be two different people.

39:50.513 --> 39:52.174
I wish I could.

39:54.183 --> 39:57.926
Is this your long-winded way of saying
that you hate these?

40:01.482 --> 40:06.226
Personally, I don't mind the bump
in your geek factor...

40:07.446 --> 40:12.236
...but, professionally, there are
these newfangled things you can try.

40:12.410 --> 40:14.366
They're called contacts.

40:17.415 --> 40:20.532
It means a lot
that you thought I had it in me.

40:24.463 --> 40:25.794
Don't worry, Smallville...

40:25.965 --> 40:29.002
...I'll only call you "Four Eyes"
every once in a while.

40:38.310 --> 40:40.847
But just so you're clear on one thing.

41:13.471 --> 41:14.927
CLARK:
Lois?

41:16.015 --> 41:17.221
Lois.

42:00.142 --> 42:02.133
[ENGLISH - US - SDH]
